00:30:32.590 --> 00:30:34.330
ERIC HAUTEMONT: So I'll
give an answer.

00:30:34.330 --> 00:30:37.060
I'll give an answer, but before
I give that answer, I

00:30:37.060 --> 00:30:39.500
need to promise everyone that
you'll be able to keep your

00:30:39.500 --> 00:30:43.180
mouth shut for the next, uh,
for the next two weeks.

00:30:43.180 --> 00:30:45.166
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:45.166 --> 00:30:48.640
ERIC HAUTEMONT: So is
that a "yes?" OK.

00:30:48.640 --> 00:30:51.005
So we'll be shipping--

00:30:51.005 --> 00:30:53.090
and I know I've been kind of
famous in the board game

00:30:53.090 --> 00:30:54.410
industry, because people--

00:30:54.410 --> 00:30:56.380
every time we ship a new version
on the iPhone, or

00:30:56.380 --> 00:30:58.730
something, people say, Android,
Android, Android.

00:30:58.730 --> 00:31:01.430
And I've actually gone to the
press a couple of years ago on

00:31:01.430 --> 00:31:03.830
record, and saying, we don't
want to do Android versions,

00:31:03.830 --> 00:31:04.480
and here's why.

00:31:04.480 --> 00:31:07.750
And I got a lot of flak for
that from board gamers.

00:31:07.750 --> 00:31:10.150
But we actually came in with--

00:31:10.150 --> 00:31:13.680
we actually came with a "Ticket
to Ride" version on

00:31:13.680 --> 00:31:15.170
the Android tablets.

00:31:15.170 --> 00:31:16.040
And I say tablets.

00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:17.600
So we work on some
of the large--

00:31:17.600 --> 00:31:19.930
I mean, one thing that is
interesting, and kind of

00:31:19.930 --> 00:31:22.510
change for a small team like
us on Android, is that you

00:31:22.510 --> 00:31:23.470
have this wide variety.

